 allowed host.&#10;&#10;@return void Does not return anything" ilk="function" line="915" lineend="923" name="wp_safe_redirect" signature="void wp_safe_redirect($location, $status = 302)"><variable ilk="argument" line="915" name="location" /><variable default="302" ilk="argument" line="915" name="status" /></scope><scope doc="Validates a URL for use in a redirect.&#10;&#10;Checks whether the $location is using an allowed host, if it has an absolute&#10;path. A plugin can therefore set or remove allowed host(s) to or from the&#10;list.&#10;&#10;If the host is not allowed, then the redirect is to $default supplied&#10;&#10;@since 2.8.1&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'allowed_redirect_hosts' on an array containing&#10;	WordPress host string and $location host string.&#10;&#10;@param string $location The redirect to validate&#10;@param string $default The value to return if $location is not allowed&#10;@return string redirect-sanitized URL" ilk="function" line="944" lineend="975" name="wp_validate_redirect" returns="string" signature="string wp_validate_redirect(string $location, string $default = '')"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="944" name="location" /><variable citdl="string" default="''" ilk="argument" line="944" name="default" /><variable citdl="parse_url()" line="953" name="lp" /><variable line="951" name="test" /><variable citdl="array()" line="969" name="allowed_hosts" /><variable citdl="parse_url()" line="967" name="wpp" /></scope><scope doc="Notify an author of a comment/trackback/pingback to one of their posts.&#10;&#10;@since 1.0.0&#10;&#10;@param int $comment_id Comment ID&#10;@param string $comment_type Optional. The comment type either 'comment' (default), 'trackback', or 'pingback'&#10;@return bool False if user email does not exist. True on completion." ilk="function" line="988" lineend="1083" name="wp_notify_postauthor" returns="bool" signature="bool wp_notify_postauthor(int $comment_id, string $comment_type = '')"><variable citdl="int"